cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of reconstructing and super-resolving intensity images from low-resolution events, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE) in the proposed pipeline. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
